(Hell was the punkLeonard Cohen in that department.)
He quips about his popularity with critics,“because they were predisposed to favor noise, intellect, and failure.” In the finalscene, he runs into his old nemesis Verlaine for the first time in years — flippingthrough the dollar bins outside the Strand Bookstore — and walks away in tears, musing, “We were like two monsters confiding.”